    "created_at": "2015-12-14T07:04:40Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-14T07:04:40Z",
    "body": "Ok per my understanding of [the code](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/e5e4749eb3c592667922f87c1105981db9dd84f7/atom/browser/api/atom_api_global_shortcut.cc#L61) `isRegistered` isn't even built to check the system, but rather just the list of shortcuts registered by the current app, is that right?\n\nIf so, that's still kinda misleading IMO in that the `globalShortcut` module should check _global_ registrations, but at least that's unsurprising that it doesn't work.\n\n_But_, `register` should still return `false`, at the least.\n"
