    "created_at": "2015-12-15T06:09:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-15T06:09:14Z",
    "body": "Yeah this API currently only checks for the shortcuts registered by this app and I agree we should make it system-wide, but I don't think it is possible for third party apps. OS X doesn't provide a public API to check whether a shortcut is registered, and the API registering shortcuts doesn't report error when a shortcut is taken by another application, I'm sure there is some private API to achieve this, but they are not documented anywhere.\n\nAlso for the example you provided, I think it is not checking for global shortcuts, it is just checking whether a shortcut is registered by a menu item used by the same application.\n\nI'm closing this as won't fix because it is technically unfixable, but if anyone finds out to do it, I'll reopen this issue.\n"
  },
