    "created_at": "2015-12-15T08:14:53Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-15T08:15:10Z",
    "body": "Ok, thanks @zcbenz. I'll note for posterity that it does appear possible to make the shortcuts truly exclusive by passing [`kEventHotKeyExclusive`](https://gist.github.com/wearhere/de49aaebb8393de0955b#file-carbonevents-h-L15424) to `RegisterEventHotKey` whereas [we currently pass 0](https://github.com/atom/electron/blob/master/chromium_src/chrome/browser/extensions/global_shortcut_listener_mac.mm#L218), in which case `register` _would_ start returning `false`; but since this would be a breaking change in terms of the API's current behavior and we still wouldn't have a way to make `isRegistered` \"work\" maybe best to leave as is.\n"
  },
